  m_Name: Bedroom Relic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Chamberstick
  description: 'A chamberstick was a small handheld candle holder used to carry light
    safely through a house at night. It was especially common in bedrooms and hallways
    before the introduction of electric lighting. The design typically included a
    handle and a drip tray to prevent wax from spilling, allowing residents or servants
    to move through dark interiors safely. '
  illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 02fd01fd929e4da49ab681a78b8fed6f, type: 3}
